self in Frente's neighborhood for eighteen months, Alarcón captures the world of the urban poor in all of its complexity and humanity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aJuvenile delinquencyzArgentinazBuenos Aires Suburban AreavCase studies. 0aMarginality, SocialzArgentinazBuenos Aires Suburban AreavCase studies. 0aViolencezArgentinazBuenos Aires Suburban AreavCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh1 aCaistor, Nick1 aLópez Levy, Marcela08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478004417zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478004417.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles